  "texts": [
    "This reduction in supply contributes to an existing global deficit, meaning that the overall availability of the commodity (likely oil, given the context of OPEC) is insufficient to meet global demand.",
    "The decrease in U.S. supplies worsens this deficit, making it even more critical for OPEC to increase its production to help balance the supply and demand in the global market.\"",
    "Demand Few Shot ExamplesQuestion:\"Diesel consumption is expected to fall to 158 million tonnes from 159.8 million last year, while gasoline demand is seen growing 3.6 per cent to 131.9 million tonnes.",
    "\"Answer:\"Netural|0.85|The decrease in diesel consumption is balanced by the increase in gasoline demand, resulting in an overall neutral effect on the total demand for these fuels.",
    "This balance means that there is no significant net change in the total demand, hence it is described as neutral."
